<TITLE> Court frames charges against Obaidul Quader </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 8 (bdnews24.com)Two Dhaka courts Tuesday framed charges against former state minister for youth and sports Obaidul Quader in twin bribery cases. The Special Judge's Court 7 and Special Judge's Court 9 set up in the Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban framed the charges. On Sept 30 last year, assistant director of the Anticorruption Commission Ashraful Islam filed three cases against the Awami League leader with Paltan Police Station. Judge Md Sirajul Islam of the Special Judge Court 7 fixed April 10 to record testimonies in one case filed for taking Tk 38 lakh in bribe. According to case details, Obaidul Quader took the money from 14 firms in 1999 in return for approval to their projects under the National Sports Council. Judge Khondoker Kamal Uzzaman framed the charges in the second case filed for taking Tk 47 lakh in bribe. The AL leader took the money from 30 agencies in 2000. Joint forces arrested Obaidul Quader on March 9 last year. bdnew
